    {
      "role": "user",
      "content": "i get the $\\alpha$ thing, but it just feels like we're ignoring real trends because of some arbitrary cutoff. sometimes the data just looks really noisy or messy, and it feels like that noise is what's pushing the p-value just past the line. how do we actually distinguish between true random error and something else interfering with the data?",
      "source": "evaluator"
    },
