      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "Quantifying unpredictable noise is quite challenging, as it often points toward complex, perhaps non-linear, processes. You might explore techniques like bootstrapping, which resamples your data many times to build an empirical distribution of your effect, giving a more robust idea of sampling variability. If the variability is consistently too high regardless of your statistical models, it could signal underlying system complexity that standard parametric tests are not designed to capture.",
      "source": "target",
